@node "Document_0" "Introducing the Programm"


                               Introduction


The TEX - ADocreader is a Databaseprogramm for Autodocs and Includes. You
also can show LVO's (Library Vector Offsets) of Librarys using the Help of
the FD Files.

The Programm is easy to use, flexible and you are even able to expand it the
way you want.

We wrote this Programm because other Software of this type didn't work
correctly, used to much Systemresources (MUI ?!) or they simply didn't give
us all the features we wanted to have.

We hopy you enjoy working with our nice Tool...
@endnode

@node "Document_1" "Installation of ADocReader"

                             How to Install it

Simply copy the Programm and it's Icon into the Directory where you want to
have it. For Tooltype and CLI parameters please look under "Starting it"
@endnode

@node "Document_2" "What do i need (part 1)"

                             Needed Programms

To use ADocReader you should have the "ReqTools.library" from Nico Francois
/ Magnus Holmgren installed in your LIBS: drawer.  We used this Library,
because it simply has the best performance for a Requestertoolkit.
Furthermore, the ReqTools Kit is the wellmost spread und used one on the
Amiga.

If you don't have the ReqTools.library in your LIBS: drawer, then you can
Download the complete kit from local BBS Systems or directly from the Aminet
under UTIL/LIBS.
@endnode

@node "Document_3" "What do i need (part 2)"

                               Needed Files

Ofcourse you should already have a few Autodocs. Without them the
AutoDocReader is senseless. If you don't have some AutoDoc Files you can
simply download some in the AMINET under DEV/MISC or sometimes you can find
them beside some released Librarys. Some Programmers put their Autodocs also
in their Library Archives.

To get the full performance of the Reader you also should have the  System
Include- and Library FD Files. These Files are also included in Autodoc
Archives.


WARNING:

AUTODOCS IN HYPERTEXT FORMAT ARE *NOT* SUPPORTED BECAUSE IT WOULD BE
HORRIBLE SENSELESS.
@endnode

